  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to analyze the effect exosomes derived from red blood cell units have
      on blood coagulation and platelet function. It is an in vitro study using healthy volunteers'
      blood.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The blood of 25 healthy volunteers will be exposed to exosomes derived from red blood cell
      units. The effects on coagulation and platelet function will be measured using
      thromboelastometry (ROTEM®) and FACS analysis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
